honeywell.printer.configuration.ez

Class BatteryCondition

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterData
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterState
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.BatteryCondition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class BatteryCondition
extends PrinterState
    This class handles the data from an {BT?} query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    CHIs the printer plugged into an AC power source
    PSPower source
    TTemperature of the battery
    VVoltage of battery
    V1Voltage of battery 1
    V2Voltage of battery 2
    VEVoltage of the battery eliminator
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • BatteryCondition

        public BatteryCondition(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer

        Indicates if getChargerConnected() parameter is present.
